      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"4. VASTUS did a good job to finish second last time out over 390m at Warrnambool (22.59) in a Grade 5, the second top-three finish on the trot. Key player on best and expected to bounce back. 2. CHALK AND CHEESE failed to come into contention last start after settling well back at Ballarat, but prior to that won by 1.5 lengths at Warragul (22.94) beating Unleash Me in a Grade 5 on April 10. Goes well out of this box with a win and four minor placings. Should be about the mark. 1. HYLAND AZULA was safely held last time out, finishing sixth at Bendigo over 425m behind Hot Ashes (24.26) in a Grade 4/5. Great chance to atone. 8. PAW UMA looks an each-way chance.\",\"runners\":[4,2,1,8],\"exclusive\":false}",
